This paper discusses the challenge of defining algorithms for autonomous vehicles to make moral decisions, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The study also involves human participants and their preferences, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and ethics in technology (cs.ET). Additionally, the study uses statistical analysis to draw conclusions, which falls under social and information sciences (cs.SI).
